  "stem": "<p>The table shows two values of x and their corresponding values of y. The graph of the linear equation representing this relationship passes through the point (12, a). What is the value of a?</p><table border=\"1\"><tr><th>x</th><th>y</th></tr><tr><td>-8</td><td>-50</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>10</td></tr></table>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "50"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Slope = (10 - (-50))/(4 - (-8)) = 60/12 = 5. Using (4, 10): y - 10 = 5(x - 4), so y = 5x - 10. At x = 12: y = 60 - 10 = 50. So a = 50.</p>",
